Narrative:
On March [XXX], 2025 at 3:15 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a first responder vehicle (unmarked police car) on [XXX] near [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was stopped facing northwest on [XXX] for a rider drop-off when an unmarked police car traveling northwest on [XXX] attempted to pass the Waymo AV.  As the police car attempted to pass by the parked Waymo AV, the passenger side of the police car made contact with the rear driver side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The police car sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On November [XXX], 2024 at 8:08 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in West Hollywood, California was in a collision involving a [XXX] SUV on [XXX] at [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was stopped facing north in a parking lot near the intersection of [XXX] at [XXX] for a passenger pickup when a passenger car entered the parking lot from the north, followed closely by the SUV. The passenger car passed the stationary Waymo AV on the left and pulled into a parking space behind and to the right of the Waymo AV. The SUV activated its lights, passed the stationary Waymo AV on the left, and then initiated a left turn behind the Waymo AV before coming to a stop near the passenger car. The SUV then pulled slightly forward and the passenger side of the SUV made contact with the driver side of the stationary Waymo AV.  At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The SUV sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01.  Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On November [XXX], 2024 at 1:18 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an ambulance on [XXX] at [XX]. 
The Waymo AV was traveling east in the leftmost of two lanes on [XXX]. While the traffic light was yellow, the Waymo AV began to cross the intersection with [XXX]. As the Waymo AV was crossing the intersection, an ambulance traveling north on [XXX] (without lights and sirens activated) began to make a right turn onto eastbound [XXX]. While the ambulance completed its right turn it crossed into the lane the Waymo AV was travling in and the front driver side of the ambulance then made contact with the rear passenger side door of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Wamo AV sustained damage. 
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On June [XXX], 2024 at 3:25 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in [XXX], California was in a collision involving an ambulance on the [XXX] of [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was stopped in the westbound lane of [XXX] for a passenger pickup when an oncoming ambulance driving east on [XXX] with lights and sirens active passed the Waymo AV. A small component on the door panel that appears to be a padlock on the driver side panel of the ambulance made contact with the front driver side tire of the Waymo AV, and the padlock became unattached from the ambulance. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On September 14, 2023, GM Cruise Holdings LLC ("Cruise") filed an update Incident Report (the "Report") under the Second Amended Standing General Order 2021-01, dated April 5, 2023 (the "Order") General Motors LLC (GM) manufactured the Cruise-operated motor vehicle involved in the incident summarized in the Incident Report. Because GM is also a Reporting Entity under the Order, GM is submitting a duplicate of the redacted public copy of the Report. GM has selected "Unknown" in the "ADS version" and "ODD time" fields solely to avoid a second submission of nonpublic Cruise CBI GM is in possession of Cruise's responses to these fields, and incorporates Cruise's responses into this submission by reference. GM's submission is based on facts supplied to GM by Cruise. GM has not investigated the alleged incident and currently believes, based on a reasonable inquiry, that it has no independent knowledge of the facts in the Report. (Reference file: 30412-6144-3).

Cruise autonomous vehicle ("AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling westbound on [XXX] between [XXX] and [XXX]. As the AV was passing through the intersection with [XXX] on a green light, a fire truck with emergency lights traveling southbound on [XXX] entered the intersection and made contact with the AV, damaging the front and rear passenger side of the AV. Police and Emergency Medical Services (EMS) were called to the scene. The AV was towed from the scene. The passenger of the AV was assessed by medical personnel at the scene and was transported by EMS. [REDACTED, MAY CONTAIN CONFIDENTIAL BUSINESS INFORMATION]

On January [XXX], 2023 at 5:36 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in Phoenix, Arizona was in a collision involving a tow truck in a parking lot near [XXX] and [XXX].
While the Waymo AV stopped in a parking lot in autonomous mode, a tow truck approached from behind the Waymo and attempted to complete a multi-point turn. While performing a multi-point turn, the tow truck reversed into the rear left sensor of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.
